### Complete and Simple Solution

```lean
/- # Exercicio 12.1
   a definição recursiva de `parts` provavelmente teria uma prova mais simples
   mas não consigo usar na prova por ser `partial`.
-/

example : ∀ xs : List Nat, (parts₁ xs).length = 2^(xs.length - 1) := by
 intro xs
 induction xs with
 | nil => simp [parts₁]
 | cons x xs ih =>
   simp_all [parts₁, List.cons_append, List.append_assoc]
   <;> cases xs <;>
   simp_all [pow_add, pow_one, mul_comm, mul_assoc, mul_left_comm, List.length]
   <;> ring_nf at *
   <;> norm_num at *
   <;> simp_all [pow_add, pow_one, mul_comm, mul_assoc, mul_left_comm, List.length]
   <;> omega
```
